__inputs.label: Prometheus
__inputs.name: DS_PROM

description: Flyte Propeller Dashboard. This is great for monitoring FlytePropeller / Flyte data plane deployments. This is mostly useful for the Flyte deployment maintainer

panels.description: The number of golang goroutines available to accept new work from the main workqueue. Each worker can process one item from the workqueue at a time.
panels.title: Free workers count

panels.description: Round success, error and total rates. Also includes total rate including streaks within a single round. The streak rate graph should match the difference between the totals with and without streaks.
panels.title: Round success/error rate

panels.description: Error rates for each type of failure that may occur as propeller is traversing the workflow DAG.
panels.title: Error rate breakdown

panels.description: Streaks are when propeller iterates over the same workflow multiple times in a single round. This is an optimisation technique.
panels.title: Streak rate

panels.description: Success vs failure rate for the various plugins used for each node e.g. k8s plugin or spark plugin.
panels.title: Plugin Success/Failure rate

panels.description: Round latency breakdown. When there are streaks within one round each iteration is measured separately.
panels.title: Round Latency (includes streak rounds)

panels.description: Round latency by workflow name. When there are streaks within one round each iteration is measured separately.
panels.title: Round traverse latency per workflow

panels.description: Count of currently running workflows running per project
panels.title: Running Workflows per project

panels.description: Rate at which workflows are being enqueued by flytepropeller. These enqueues all pass through the sub-queue before going back into the main queue.
panels.title: Workflow enqueue rate

panels.description: Rate at which items are actually added to the queue. If an item is already on the queue attempting to add it will be a no-op. Usually there is also rate limiting that will delay items from being added to the queue.
panels.title: Add rate to queue

panels.description: Tracks every rate limited add synchronously before rate limiting delays or deduplication
panels.title: Add rate before rate limiting and deduplication

panels.description: The number of items that are currently in the queue but have not been processed yet.
panels.title: Unprocessed Queue depth

panels.description: Sum of the current in progress time of every in progress item in the queue.
panels.title: Seconds of unfinished work in progress
Metastore read open latency by workflow
Node Exec latency quantile and workflow
Node Input latency quantile and workflow
Node Event event recording latency quantile and workflow
node event recording error rate breakdown

panels.description: Cache hit rate when admin launcher is queried for the status of a workflow. Admin launcher will update status of workflows in the cache on a polling interval.
panels.title: Admin Launcher cache hit/miss rate
Update events drop rate becacuse they have the same resource version

title: Flyte Propeller Dashboard (via Prometheus)
